# Code owners for QARoom's INVARIANT SOURCES (verifiable-invariants experiment, ADR-0024 Phase 4).
#
# These paths are single-source-of-truth definitions: a Zod contract here is derived into the DB
# constraint, the runtime validator, the OpenAPI doc, and the property generator; a TLA+ spec here
# is bound to the delivery worker. Weakening one quietly weakens every enforcement downstream — the
# exact failure mode the experiment exists to prevent. They require a HUMAN (not bot) review.
#
# This file only ASSIGNS owners. To make owner review REQUIRED, the repo owner must enable, in
# Settings -> Branches -> branch protection for `main`: "Require a pull request before merging" +
# "Require review from Code Owners". Until then this is advisory (paired with the invariant-guard
# workflow, which flags any PR touching these paths).

# The Zod schema authority — the one definition the whole derivation chain hangs off.
/packages/contracts/**            @mariusargatu

# Formal specs (TLA+ and any future spec/ models) bound to runtime assertions.
/spec/**                          @mariusargatu

# The falsifiable-claim + detection-matrix + boundary manifests: the single source for what is
# provably guarded and how each claim is taxonomised.
/scripts/lib/manifests/claims.ts            @mariusargatu
/scripts/lib/manifests/detection-matrix.ts  @mariusargatu
/scripts/lib/manifests/boundary-registry.ts @mariusargatu

# The DERIVATION CHAIN (T23, ADR-0033). Governing the source (the Zod / VOTE_VALUES above) is not
# enough: the cheapest tamper leaves the invariant pristine and weakens what DERIVES from it — the
# property generators, the mutation config (mutated paths + survival threshold), and the prove/teeth
# harness itself. Each is now a Code-Owned single point, so an agent cannot quietly loosen the chain
# below the codeowned source. (See also gate-guard.yml, which flags a gate edited alongside its target.)
